1. Functional requirements

   - System shall allow users to register account.
   - System shall allow users to log in and log out securely.
   - System shall allow users to link bank accounts.
   - System shall allow users to view list of accounts + balances.
   - System shall allow users to view detailed transaction history.
   - System shall allow users to filter transaction history
   - System shall allow users to transfer between own accounts.
   - System shall allow users to transfer to other customers
   - System shall validate balance before transfer.
   - System shall allow users to register and manage payees.
   - System shall allow users to pay bills.
   - System shall record all operations as transactions
   - System shall store customersâ€™ profile data.
   - System shall log important events.
   - System shall support one-time bill payments.
   - System shall support repetitive (recurring) bill payments.

2. Non-functional requirements
   - UI shall be user-friendly.
   - System shall be Secured
   - System shall ensure consistency and atomic operations.
   - System shall provide acceptable performance
   - System shall be available during normal banking hours with minimal downtime.
   - System shall be scalable
   - System shall be maintainable
   - System shall be cost-efficiency
   - System shall have a good performance
